"value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<figure class=\"table-container\"><table class=\"properties\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Type</th>\n      <td><code>String</code></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table></figure>\n<p>The <code>background_color</code> member defines a placeholder background color for the application page to display before its stylesheet is loaded. This value is used by the user agent to draw the background color of a shortcut when the manifest is available before the stylesheet has loaded.</p>\n<p>Therefore <code>background_color</code> should match the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-color\"><code>background-color</code></a> CSS property in the site's stylesheet for a smooth transition between launching the web application and loading the site's content.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> The <code>background_color</code> member is only meant to improve the user experience while the main stylesheet is loading from the network or the storage media; it is not used by the user agent as the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-color\"><code>background-color</code></a> CSS property when the progressive web app stylesheet is available.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">json</span></p><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token property\">\"background_color\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"red\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/manifest/#background_color-member","title":"Web Application Manifest"}],"query":"html.manifest.background_color"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"html.manifest.background_color"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The background_color member defines a placeholder background color for the application page to display before its stylesheet is loaded. This value is used by the user agent to draw the background color of a shortcut when the manifest is available before the stylesheet has loaded.","popularity":0.0047,"modified":"2023-06-28T16:16:20.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/manifest/background_color","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/manifest/background_color/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/0c015b80f786ecc4547c3e37a70c7f6aafdfbf74","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"background_color","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest","title":"Web app manifests"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/background_color","title":"background_color"}],"pageTitle":"background_color - Web app manifests | MDN","noIndexing":false}}